radiographic_examinations.findings: The liver enhances homogeneously without concerning lesions or biliary dilatation. The gallbladder, spleen, pancreas and adrenal glands are unremarkable. Kidneys enhance and excrete symmetrically without concerning lesions or hydronephrosis. Stomach is distended with ingested material and non-dilated loops of small bowel are normal in course and caliber without wall thickening or sign of obstruction. Colon is within normal limits. A large appendicolith measuring approximately 12 mm is present at the base of the appendix resulting in a fluid-filled appendix that is dilated up to 1.2 cm with mild adjacent fat stranding. A second appendicolith is also present more distally. There is no evidence of perforation at this time. There is no mesenteric or retroperitoneal lymphadenopathy. There is no intra-abdominal free air or fluid. Bladder is partially decompressed. Seminal vesicles and prostate gland are unremarkable. There is no pelvic free fluid or lymphadenopathy. No concerning osteolytic or sclerotic lesion identified. Abdominal aorta is of normal caliber without aneurysmal dilatation.
